  "@type": "SolutionRecord",
  "@id": "ocp:github/zalando-incubator--kube-aws-iam-controller",
  "meta": {
    "title": "AWS IAM Controller for Kubernetes",
    "description": "Distribute different AWS IAM credentials to different pods in Kubernetes via secrets.",
    "version": "1.0.0",
    "dateCreated": "2026-03-10T05:02:41.218Z",
    "dateModified": "2026-03-10T05:02:41.218Z",
    "keywords": [
      "aws",
      "golang",
      "iam",
      "kubernetes",
      "modules",
      "robust",
      "sdk"
    ],
    "license": "MIT"
  },
  "problemSolved": {
    "statement": "[![Build Status](https://travis-ci.org/zalando-incubator/kube-aws-iam-controller.svg?branch=master)](https://travis-ci.org/zalando-incubator/kube-aws-iam-controller)\n[![Coverage Status](https://coveralls.io/repos/github/zalando-incubator/kube-aws-iam-controller/badge.svg?branch=master)](https://coveralls.io/github/zalando-incubator/kube-aws-iam-controller?branch=master)",
    "context": "[![Build Status](https://travis-ci.org/zalando-incubator/kube-aws-iam-controller.svg?branch=master)](https://travis-ci.org/zalando-incubator/kube-aws-iam-controller)\n[![Coverage Status](https://coveralls.io/repos/github/zalando-incubator/kube-aws-iam-controller/badge.svg?branch=master)](https://coveralls.io/github/zalando-incubator/kube-aws-iam-controller?branch=master)\n\nThis is a Kubernetes controller for distributing AWS IAM role credentials to\npods via secrets.\n\nIt aims to solve the same problem as other existing tools like\n[jtblin/kube2iam](https://github.com/jtblin/kube2iam) and\n[uswitch/kiam](https://github.com/uswitch/kiam), namely distribute different\nAWS IAM roles to different pods within the same cluster.  However, it solves\nthe problem in a different way to work around an inherit problem with the\narchitecture or kube2iam and similar solutions.",
    "cynefinDomain": "complex"
  },
